      "content": "To: All Onboarding Team Members\n\nSubject: Enhancing GDPR Compliance in Client Onboarding Process\n\nAs we continue to prioritize our commitment to GDPR compliance, we are implementing the following protocols to ensure our client onboarding process meets the necessary requirements.\n\nWhen collecting client data, we will implement data minimization principles to ensure that we only collect the minimum amount of personal data necessary to provide our services. This may involve requesting only the necessary fields for the specific service or product being offered. Our data collection forms will clearly indicate the purpose of data collection and obtain explicit consent from the client where required.\n\nOnce collected, we will store client data in accordance with storage limitation principles. All client data will be stored for the minimum necessary period, and we will implement technical and organizational measures to ensure the integrity and confidentiality of the data. This may include encryption, secure data centers, and access controls.\n\nWhen processing client data, we will ensure that we have a lawful basis for doing so. This may involve obtaining explicit consent from the client or relying on legitimate interests, such as providing a service to the client. We will also maintain accurate records of client data, including the purpose of data processing and the rights of the client.\n\nOur data protection officer (DPO) will",
